        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 9:51AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 951 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fort McClellan, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hollis Crossroads, Muscadine, Abernathy, Sweetwater Lake, Coleman
Lake And Campground, Edwardsville, Trickem, Lake Cleburne, Heflin, I
20 Welcome Center, Liberty Hill, Chalafinnee, Oak Level, Ranburne,
Fruithurst, Borden Springs, Mars Hills, and Camp Sequoyah.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until noon CDT for
northeastern and east central Alabama.</instruction>
